This paper is primarily focused on image super-resolution using deep learning techniques, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of transfer learning and meta-learning, which are common topics in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of neural networks (cs.NE) and the application of the proposed method to a wide range of image conditions (cs.MM).
